stylometry: RISKSIMTABLE allows you to run mutiple simulations at the same time using different numbers of the input variable. The input variable is usually the decision variable. RISKSIMTABLE is useful because you can see all the simulations and it is easy to compare to results at the same time. Say you wanted to figure out how much to order and your different order quantities that you are trying are 100, 150, 200, 250 and 300. Using RISKSIMTABLE, you would run simulations on all of these quatntities at the same time. You would then compare all of the results to see which one is the best.
